AWS Account                — Trust boundary
 ├─ IAM                    — Identity control
 │   ├─ User               — Human credentials
 │   ├─ Role               — Temporary permissions
 │   ├─ Policy             — Allowed actions
 │   └─ Access Key         — Programmatic entry
 │
 ├─ Network (VPC)          — Isolation boundary
 │   ├─ VPC                — Virtual network
 │   ├─ Subnet             — Network segment
 │   ├─ Route Table        — Traffic direction
 │   ├─ Internet Gateway   — Public exposure
 │   ├─ NAT Gateway        — Outbound access
 │   └─ VPC Peering        — Lateral movement
 │
 ├─ Edge Layer             — First contact
 │   ├─ Route53            — DNS discovery
 │   ├─ CloudFront         — CDN & cache
 │   ├─ WAF                — Request filtering
 │   └─ Load Balancer      — Traffic distributor
 │
 ├─ Compute                — Execution target
 │   ├─ EC2                — Virtual machine
 │   │   ├─ OS             — Privilege boundary
 │   │   ├─ Process        — Running service
 │   │   ├─ Thread         — Execution unit
 │   │   └─ Memory         — Exploitable state
 │   │
 │   ├─ ECS / EKS          — Container runtime
 │   │   ├─ Pod / Task     — Workload unit
 │   │   └─ Container      — App sandbox
 │   │
 │   └─ Lambda             — Serverless execution
 │       ├─ Handler        — Entry function
 │       └─ Role           — Permission scope
 │
 ├─ Application Layer      — Main attack surface
 │   ├─ API Gateway        — HTTP entry point
 │   ├─ REST API           — Endpoints & methods
 │   │   ├─ Endpoint       — URL path
 │   │   ├─ Method         — GET / POST / PUT
 │   │   ├─ Auth           — JWT / IAM / Cognito
 │   │   └─ Payload        — JSON input
 │   │
 │   └─ Service Logic      — Business code
 │
 ├─ Data Layer             — High‑value target
 │   ├─ S3                 — Object storage
 │   ├─ RDS                — Relational database
 │   ├─ DynamoDB           — NoSQL store
 │   └─ Secrets Manager    — Credentials vault
 │
 ├─ Messaging              — Async attack paths
 │   ├─ SQS                — Queue abuse
 │   ├─ SNS                — Fan‑out injection
 │   └─ EventBridge        — Trigger chaining
 │
 ├─ Observability          — Detection surface
 │   ├─ CloudWatch         — Logs & metrics
 │   ├─ CloudTrail         — API activity
 │   └─ VPC Flow Logs      — Network traces
 │
 └─ Metadata & Control     — Privilege escalation
     ├─ Instance Metadata  — IAM role leakage
     ├─ STS                — Temporary creds
     └─ Control Plane APIs — Full account access


Hacker’s AWS Kill‑Chain (One‑Line)
DNS → ALB → API → Input → Compute → IAM Role → Metadata → AWS APIs → Data
